<br>
The bottom line is that 2.5-3 groups made the ring fun (hard, continual fighting, but fun), but weren't enough for the bosses.  Adding more people made the whole ring very boring (well ahead of respawn, etc) but let you do more bosses.<br>
<br>
Given L65, and better gear than what we had, 3 groups might handle even the biggest bosses.  The loot table seems spread out through the bosses to a degree, but each one has their own toys.  You might have to fight for 4 hours to get an interesting boss, and you might have to fight for 5 minutes.<br>
<br>
You need enough people and plans to be able to tank deathtouching bosses while still fighting the ring (spawn doesn't stop while you're killing a boss; you used to be able to get multiple bosses at once if you were &quot;lucky&quot;.  Not sure if that's still the case).<br>
<br>
Depending on your levels and gear 18-24 I'd estimate to &quot;learn&quot; the ring and be able to deal with the harder bosses.  Just expect some of them to have rather nasty abilities, so be prepared to switch tanks.<br>
<br>
It's been ages since we've stuck our nose in there though.  The ring is so close to what it should be, yet in a couple of ways so, so far.  Deathtouch and the fact that the ring continues to spawn while you fight a boss are the major issues it has.  If the ring didn't spawn, you wouldn't need as many people and could have alot more fun.<br>
<br>
My info is dated though so your mileage may vary.<br>
<br>
-- Hika <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=onomatopoeia>onomatopoeia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 152<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/30/03 4:37:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26318.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.chater.demon.co.uk/boyatbook.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:About the Ring of Fire quest</span><hr size=1> It's much harder than Hika describes now.  Right from the start 3 mobs spawn per wave, have about 20khps each and they spawn often (60 or 90 seconds I think).<br>
<br>
